    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would use `appId` and `apiKey`:\n\nDo not have to remember that \"application id\" is named \"applicationID\" (uppercase I and D). A bit like the mighty getElementByID (took me some time to correct my typing when using it).\n\nDo not have to remember the upper case `APIK` token.\n\nAbout preventing people to put an \"admin key\" inside a webpage: we already warn them everywhere and we still get issues about it. I am not sure naming it \"searchOnlyAPIKey\" would help. People putting sensitive data inside a web page will still do it.\n\nWe already document \"appId\" and \"apiKey\" inside the [client](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-js#browserify-webpack) and [helper](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js#example) (and yes I wrote those examples).\n",
    "created_at": "2015-09-14T11:59:52Z",
